FL,424,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F423A1779117068
OL,3,CSchools shut over fears play sand
OL,4,Ccould contain asbestos
OL,6,FThe closures at Beacon Hill School, in
OL,7,FWallsend, Silverdale School, in
OL,8,FHowdon, and Woodlawn School, in
OL,9,FWhitley Bay - come following a
OL,10,Fnational product recall of almost 40
OL,11,Fitems sold by supermarkets and high
OL,12,Fstreet stores.
OL,14,FResults from testing at Silverdale
OL,15,FSchool are understood to have been
OL,16,Fnegative - and the school is expected
OL,17,Fto be open on Friday. Beacon Hill
OL,18,FSchool is awaiting its results.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,424,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F423A1779117068
OL,3,CSchools shut over fears play sand
OL,4,Ccould contain asbestos
OL,6,FOn Tuesday, Woodlawn School saw seven
OL,7,Fclassrooms closed. They have all since
OL,8,Freopened following negative test
OL,9,Fresults.
OL,11,FRetailers including Tesco, Primark,
OL,12,FMatalan, Smyths Toys, The Entertainer,
OL,13,FAldi, Argos, Asda and M&S have taken
OL,14,Fthe toys off shelves after they were
OL,15,Ffound to contain the substance, recall
OL,16,Finformation on the Office for Product
OL,17,FSafety and Standards (OPSS) website
OL,18,Fshowed in April.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
